     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Top misrouting pairs (true ≠ predicted), most frequent first.\n",
    "mis = []\n",
    "for i in range(len(ROUTES)):\n",
    "    for j in range(len(ROUTES)):\n",
    "        if i != j and cm[i, j] > 0:\n",
    "            mis.append((cm[i, j], ROUTES[i], ROUTES[j]))\n",
    "mis.sort(reverse=True)\n",
    "print(\"Most common misroutes (count | TRUE → PREDICTED):\")\n",
    "for n, t, p in mis[:8]:\n",
    "    print(f\"  {n:3d} | {t}  →  {p}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "243e3aca",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Reading the errors.** Confusions cluster where queues are *semantically\n",
    "adjacent* — e.g. a declined card payment (*Card Operations*) reads a lot like a\n",
    "declined transfer (*Payments & Transfers*), and an unexpected fee (*Fees/Rates*)\n",
    "overlaps with a duplicate charge (*Card Disputes*). These are exactly the cases\n",
    "where **top-3** rescues routing usefulness, and where a confidence threshold\n",
    "should defer to a human."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
