     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Macro-F1  | zero-shot: Granite 0.674 vs Qwen 0.682  (Δ -0.008)\n",
      "Macro-F1  | fine-tuned: Granite 0.971 vs Qwen 0.958  (Δ +0.013)\n",
      "Params    | Qwen ~1.5B vs Granite ~3B   (~2x)\n",
      "Train VRAM| Qwen ~5.1 GB vs Granite ~4.2 GB  (micro-batch 2 for 3B)\n",
      "Calib ECE | Granite FT 0.377 vs Qwen FT 0.360\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "d_zs = g_zs['macro_f1'] - metrics_base['macro_f1']\n",
    "d_ft = g_ft['macro_f1'] - metrics_ft['macro_f1']\n",
    "print(f\"Macro-F1  | zero-shot: Granite {g_zs['macro_f1']:.3f} vs Qwen {metrics_base['macro_f1']:.3f}  (Δ {d_zs:+.3f})\")\n",
    "print(f\"Macro-F1  | fine-tuned: Granite {g_ft['macro_f1']:.3f} vs Qwen {metrics_ft['macro_f1']:.3f}  (Δ {d_ft:+.3f})\")\n",
    "print(f\"Params    | Qwen ~1.5B vs Granite ~3B   (~2x)\")\n",
    "print(f\"Train VRAM| Qwen ~5.1 GB vs Granite ~{g_peak:.1f} GB  (micro-batch {2} for 3B)\")\n",
    "print(f\"Calib ECE | Granite FT {g_ft['ece']:.3f} vs Qwen FT {metrics_ft['ece']:.3f}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "95dee65b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Reading the comparison (actual numbers above).**\n",
    "- **Zero-shot ≈ tie on F1, but Granite is far better *calibrated*.** The two\n",
    "  backbones land within ~0.01 macro-F1 of each other zero-shot, yet Granite-3B'''s\n",
    "  zero-shot **ECE is ~0.08 vs Qwen'''s ~0.18** — its confidences are trustworthy\n",
    "  out of the box, which is exactly what confidence-gated routing needs.\n",
    "- **Fine-tuned ceiling is saturated.** QLoRA pushes *both* to ~0.96–0.97\n",
    "  macro-F1; Granite edges ahead by only ~+0.01. On an 8-way task the 1.5B already\n",
    "  nearly solves, **2× the parameters buys almost nothing after fine-tuning.**\n",
    "- **Cost:** comparable train VRAM here (Granite ran at micro-batch 2, ~4 GB), but\n",
    "  the 3B is ~2× the compute per scored candidate → slower inference. Note **both**\n",
    "  models''' ECE *rises* after fine-tuning (over-confidence) — temperature-scale\n",
    "  before deploying either.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Recommendation.** For this routing task, **stick with the 1.5B** — same\n",
    "fine-tuned quality, cheaper and faster. Granite-3B is compelling only if you need\n",
    "its stronger *zero-shot* behaviour/calibration (little fine-tuning data), or for\n",
    "the harder hierarchical **L2** step in the companion triage project — where extra\n",
    "capacity is more likely to pay off."
   ]
  }
 ],
